cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper presents a novel approach for vanishing point detection using a convolutional neural network (CNN), which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of synthetic data for training and the elimination of the need for labelled images suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the detection of lines in an image, which is a common problem in computer graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO).
